item.title: Prawn industry using hi-tech forensics
item.description: The Australian prawn industry has adopted an aggressive strategy to verify where stock is coming from and if its being produced in an environmentally-friendly way.

item.title: Hotel quarantine backflip angers Roar players
item.description: Brisbane Roar players are furious after being told they will have to serve a two-week quarantine period in a hotel after their involvement in the A-League finals series is over.

item.title: Decision time in first pandemic poll
item.description: Chief Minister Michael Gunner is set to return be returned to the NT’s top job but without a clear majority.

item.title: NSW big chill here to stay
item.description: Snow and wild weather across NSW are expected to ease on Sunday however strong winds are expected to keep residents rugged up.

item.title: New virus outbreaks at two hospitals
item.description: The Department of Health is investigating new coronavirus outbreaks at two Melbourne hospitals.

item.title: Defrosting cars targeted in big chill
item.description: Drivers are being warned of the dangers of leaving cars unattended to defrost after a spate of alleged thefts in the ACT.

item.title: Hotel guard sparks virus investigation
item.description: A second Sydney hotel quarantine guard who tested positive to coronavirus has sparked an urgent investigation by NSW authorities.

item.title: Daft excuses for not wearing masks
item.description: A man who refused to wear a face mask because “his solicitor told him not to” was one of 161 people caught flouting lockdown laws across Victoria in the past 24 hours.

item.title: Homicide cops probe woman’s death
item.description: A man has been arrested after the suspicious death of a woman on the Sunshine Coast early Saturday morning.

item.title: Robbery victim’s surprise discovery
item.description: An Adelaide man had his wallet stolen while at a bus stop then returned home to find he had also been stabbed several times in the buttocks, police have said.
